cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

This paper deals with deep learning models and their adaptation to new domains, specifically in the context of computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of a domain confusion loss, which is a common technique in domain adaptation and transfer learning, suggesting that it could also fit into the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of a metric for model selection, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper focuses on visual domain adaptation, which could also place it in the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
